definition.value: Catalysis of the removal of a methyl group from a histone.
Catalysis of the removal of a methyl group from lysine at position 4 of the histone H3 protein.

Catalysis of the reaction -  histone H3 N6-methyl-L-lysine (position 9) + alpha-ketoglutarate + O2 -eq- succinate + CO2 + formaldehyde + lysine. This reaction is the removal of a methyl group from lysine at position 9 of the histone H3 protein.
Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the division of the cytoplasm of a cell and its separation into two daughter cells.
Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the division of the cytoplasm of a cell, and its separation into two daughter cells.
Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the division of the cytoplasm of a cell, and its separation into two daughter cells.

label.value: cytoplasmic side of mitochondrial outer membrane

definition.value: The external (cytoplasmic) face of the mitochondrial outer membrane.
A complex that possesses di-trans,poly-cis-decaprenylcistransferase activity -  involved in ubiquinone biosynthesis.
A homodimeric complex that possesses di-trans,poly-cis-decaprenylcistransferase activity -  involved in ubiquinone biosynthesis.

A heterotetrameric complex located in the mitochondrial inner membrane that possesses di-trans,poly-cis-decaprenylcistransferase activity -  involved in ubiquinone biosynthesis. In S. pombe it is a heterotetramer of Dlp1 and Dps1.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently, in a non-covalent manner, with muramyl dipeptide -  muramyl dipeptide is derived from peptidoglycan.
A cellular process that is involved in cytokinesis (the division of the cytoplasm of a cell and its separation into two daughter cells).
A protein complex formed by the association of superoxide dismutase 1 (SOD1) with calcineurin -  complex formation is implicated in activation of calcineurin by SOD1.
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  ATP + H2O + amino acid(in) --gt- ADP + phosphate + amino acid(out).
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  ATP + H2O + cysteine(in) --gt- ADP + phosphate + cysteine(out).
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  ATP + H2O + amino acid(out) --gt- ADP + phosphate + amino acid(in).
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  ATP + H2O + D-methionine(in) --gt- ADP + phosphate + D-methionine(out).
Catalysis of the transfer of a solute or solutes from one side of a membrane to the other according to the reaction -  ATP + H2O + D-methionine(out) --gt- ADP + phosphate + D-methionine(in).
Catalysis of the transfer of silicon from the inside of the cell to the outside of the cell across a membrane.
A cortical network of highly dynamic tubules that are juxtaposed to the plasma membrane and undergo ring closure and tubule-branching movements.
Catalysis of the reaction -  peroxiredoxin-(S-hydroxy-S-oxocysteine) + ATP + 2 R-SH -eq- peroxiredoxin-(S-hydroxycysteine) + ADP + phosphate + R-S-S-R.
A protein complex that is involved in the transcription of ribosomal genes. In Saccharomyces this complex consists of Ckb2p, Utp22p, Rrp7p and Ifh1p.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a deoxyribonucleoside, a compound consisting of a purine or pyrimidine nitrogenous base linked to deoxyribose.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a purine deoxyribonucleoside, a compound consisting of a purine base linked to deoxyribose.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with a pyrimidine deoxyribonucleoside, a compound consisting of a pyrimidine base linked to deoxyribose.

Interacting selectively and non-covalently with dGDP, deoxyguanosine diphosphate.
Interacting selectively and non-covalently with dGTP, deoxyguanosine triphosphate.
Catalysis of the unwinding of an RNA helix in the direction 5' to 3'.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + H2O -eq- ADP + phosphate -  this reaction drives the unwinding of an RNA helix in the direction 5' to 3'.
Catalysis of the transfer of a linoleoyl ((9Z,12Z)-octadeca-9,12-dienoyl) group to an oxygen atom on the acceptor molecule.

The lipid bilayer surrounding an aleurone grain.

A fibrous network that is part of the hyalin layer extracellular matrix. The apical lamina is thought to be principally composed of the glycoproteins fibropellins. This matrix has been found in echinoderms.
